ng and adapting to cultural difference. We see that all sojourners, from tourists, to expatriates to immigrants, go through a similar learning dynamic. We learn that intercultural experiences can be deep or shallow, and that hidden cultural difference can increase sojourner prejudice. The book examines intercultural sensitivity while avoiding “feel good” idealizations about cross-cultural contact. It brings clarity to debates regarding the importance of cultural difference and the effects of globalization. An essential resource for sojourners, language teachers and intercultural educators.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aIntercultural communication. 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teaching. 0aMulticultural education. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  acultural differences.  aglobal mobility.  aglobalisation.  aintercultural communication.  aintercultural learning.  amigration.1 aKelly, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311102473808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z97831106067130 cprintz978184769017340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184769018040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847690180423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847690180/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-102473-8  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_